       <h3>FASTLANE HYPERMARKET</h3> 

        Fastlane HyperMarket, Botswana’s Bountiful Granary came into existence in 2002 and was the first company to list on the Botswana Stock Exchange in 2005. 
            We are proud to proclaim that to this day, after over 20 years of operation and an ever-changing business environment, our Group remains the 
            only listed company without a controlling shareholder. This allows us to maintain our status as a truly Botswana company, made for the people 
            of Botswana, by the people of Botswana. <br />
            
            As a Group, we are dedicated to our customers and to maximising return for our Shareholders, whilst at the same time improving the wellbeing 
            of our employees, the people of Botswana and those in other regions where we are present. Each of our business units is driven by an experienced 
            and empowered management team, supported and overseen by our Head Office. Our management principles and performance underpin the way in which we 
            operate. Our staff compliment has increased considerably from just 233 people in 2007 to over 5,100 people in 2021, attesting Fastlanes’s promise 
            of sustainability and capability of being an employer of choice!A promise we make to our stakeholders is to continue unlocking value to expand 
            our capabilities and deliver..........
        The quality service and solutions requested by our customers
            a safe and conducive working environment for our people
            positive, sound returns for our investors and shareholders
            a trusted household name, a brand of choice for future generations
            transparency in the form of interactive communication and open access to information.

